</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E12E4AF7C5D55FF10AB687760DF75" authorityName="Bierig" authorityYear="1940" box="[136,268,1323,1346]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Megarthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mastiger">
<emphasis id="B92AB575AF7C5D55FF10AB687760DF75" box="[136,268,1323,1346]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">M. mastiger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
share a laterobasally broadly notched pronotum. Among these species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E12E4AF7C5D55FF10AB087762DF55" authorityName="Bierig" authorityYear="2011" box="[136,270,1355,1378]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Megarthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adelphus">
<emphasis id="B92AB575AF7C5D55FF10AB087762DF55" box="[136,270,1355,1378]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">M. adelphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily distinguished the lateral contour of its pronotum forming four denticles.
</paragraph>
